looking for grace is a 2015 australian drama film directed by sue brooks .   it was screened in the main competition section of the 72nd venice international film festival and in the inaugural platform section at the 2015 toronto international film festival .   the film was the first film to be directed by an australian female director to screen at the venice international film festival in 15 years .   the film stars odessa young as grace , her parents denise and dan played by radha mitchell and richard roxburgh , respectively .   the story follows grace , as she runs away from home to the wheatbelt of western australia .   her parents hire a private detective in an attempt to find her .